{"ts":"2026-06-26T21:57:06.063Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Crafting the Marketplace Narrative**\n\nI'm now establishing the narrative framework for the marketplace. It will serve as GFF AI's \"Sovereign Agent & Accelerator Marketplace,\" not a typical e-commerce platform. It is a strategic catalog targeting enterprise leaders, and highlighting certified multi-agent patterns, workflows, and architectures. It's designed to showcase immediate deployment options within a sovereign environment, and highlight how the options integrate into the Garage, Foundry, and Factory framework, emphasizing performance and fit. I am using an interactive \"Architectural Command Center\" metaphor with blueprint-like components, dark themes, and cybernetic color accents.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-26T21:57:07.958Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Designing the UI Elements**\n\nI'm now focusing on the user interface components. I envision cryptographic elements, interactive DAG flowcharts, and a floating comparison dock. This dock will function like a tactical asset loader, allowing users to compare performance metrics and integration adapters of up to three blueprints.\n\nI'm now focusing on the layout. I'm prioritizing a premium hero area with a subtle background mesh and bold copywriting, along with a unified filter bar, and an interactive grid composed of custom-designed cards. The cards will include category badges, GFF tier tags, pattern names, use case summaries, and visual cues like compliance ratings.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-26T21:57:09.905Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Refining Interaction Mechanics**\n\nI'm now zeroing in on the finer interaction details of the marketplace. I'm focusing on displaying name, use case (with italic styling), description, and related capabilities as prominent features. The footer will provide \"Add to Compare\" actions alongside CTAs for sandbox runs or agent contact. A floating, glassmorphic comparison drawer is now my focal point. It accommodates selected patterns with visual connectors. \"Analyze Comparison\" will display side-by-side schemas, prompts, data, and metrics. Moreover, I've outlined a standard \"Blueprints Anatomy\" section with details about safety wrappers and a visual grid.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-26T21:57:11.339Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Implementing Mobile Interactions**\n\nI'm now focusing on mobile optimization, specifically touch-friendly category lists with horizontal scrolling. I'm also planning the compact behavior of the comparison drawer for smaller devices: a badge that expands to a full-screen bottom sheet on tap, or gracefully scales to prevent horizontal overflows. On smaller screens, the grid will condense to a single column with optimized padding. I'm prioritizing these changes in `/app/build/marketplace/page.tsx`, understanding that `/app/page.tsx` and `/app/platforms/agent-marketplace/page.tsx` are off-limits. I'm also ensuring the quick search updates filtered results immediately, and I've designed a sleek \"No results found - Reset filters\" state with a custom blueprint request option.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-26T21:57:12.566Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Defining Agent Blueprint Data**\n\nI'm now focusing on creating a comprehensive data structure for each agent, emphasizing detailed, realistic enterprise-level descriptions. I'm prioritizing rich metadata over placeholder names to enhance the quality of my agents. I've drafted a list of eight categories, and two top-tier blueprints per category for a total of sixteen agents. My first agent is the Sovereign Research Synthesizer with its detailed specifications.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
