{"ts":"2026-06-26T21:57:37.208Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Defining the Marketplace Pages**\n\nI'm now focusing on the `/platforms/agent-marketplace` page. It's linked from other platform pages. My aim is to evolve `/build/marketplace` into a premium agent and accelerator catalog page within the directory.\n\n\n**Analyzing Component Options**\n\nI'm now investigating components imported into `/platforms/agent-marketplace/page.tsx` to understand the current build. I'm focusing on creating a premium agent and accelerator catalog, paying close attention to the requirements to design an exceptional user experience with animations, filtering, and categorization, and leveraging local static data. I need to design something special.\n\n\n**Categorizing Agent Patterns**\n\nI'm now diving into the agent categories and identifying the types we need to feature. I've drafted a comprehensive list encompassing Knowledge, Operations, Compliance, Customer Experience, Executive, Document Intelligence, Procurement, and HR agents. Next, I plan to build out magnificent agent patterns within each of these categories.\n\n\n**Detailing Agent Metadata**\n\nI'm now detailing each agent pattern with metadata including the name, category, description, use case, GFF fit, related capabilities, industry, function, maturity stage, platform fit, schema, datasources, performance metrics, and system prompts. This detailed approach aims to capture every aspect for a more comprehensive catalog listing. I'm focusing on providing concise and effective metadata to enhance the clarity and searchability of the agent descriptions.\n\n\n**Crafting the Marketplace Narrative**\n\nI'm now establishing the narrative framework for the marketplace. It will serve as GFF AI's \"Sovereign Agent & Accelerator Marketplace,\" not a typical e-commerce platform. It is a strategic catalog targeting enterprise leaders, and highlighting certified multi-agent patterns, workflows, and architectures. It's designed to showcase immediate deployment options within a sovereign environment, and highlight how the options integrate into the Garage, Foundry, and Factory framework, emphasizing performance and fit. I am using an interactive \"Architectural Command Center\" metaphor with blueprint-like components, dark themes, and cybernetic color accents.\n\n\n**Designing the UI Elements**\n\nI'm now focusing on the user interface components. I envision cryptographic elements, interactive DAG flowcharts, and a floating comparison dock. This dock will function like a tactical asset loader, allowing users to compare performance metrics and integration adapters of up to three blueprints.\n\nI'm now focusing on the layout. I'm prioritizing a premium hero area with a subtle background mesh and bold copywriting, along with a unified filter bar, and an interactive grid composed of custom-designed cards. The cards will include category badges, GFF tier tags, pattern names, use case summaries, and visual cues like compliance ratings.\n\n\n**Refining Interaction Mechanics**\n\nI'm now zeroing in on the finer interaction details of the marketplace. I'm focusing on displaying name, use case (with italic styling), description, and related capabilities as prominent features. The footer will provide \"Add to Compare\" actions alongside CTAs for sandbox runs or agent contact. A floating, glassmorphic comparison drawer is now my focal point. It accommodates selected patterns with visual connectors. \"Analyze Comparison\" will display side-by-side schemas, prompts, data, and metrics. Moreover, I've outlined a standard \"Blueprints Anatomy\" section with details about safety wrappers and a visual grid.\n\n\n**Implementing Mobile Interactions**\n\nI'm now focusing on mobile optimization, specifically touch-friendly category lists with horizontal scrolling. I'm also planning the compact behavior of the comparison drawer for smaller devices: a badge that expands to a full-screen bottom sheet on tap, or gracefully scales to prevent horizontal overflows. On smaller screens, the grid will condense to a single column with optimized padding. I'm prioritizing these changes in `/app/build/marketplace/page.tsx`, understanding that `/app/page.tsx` and `/app/platforms/agent-marketplace/page.tsx` are off-limits. I'm also ensuring the quick search updates filtered results immediately, and I've designed a sleek \"No results found - Reset filters\" state with a custom blueprint request option.\n\n\n**Defining Agent Blueprint Data**\n\nI'm now focusing on creating a comprehensive data structure for each agent, emphasizing detailed, realistic enterprise-level descriptions. I'm prioritizing rich metadata over placeholder names to enhance the quality of my agents. I've drafted a list of eight categories, and two top-tier blueprints per category for a total of sixteen agents. My first agent is the Sovereign Research Synthesizer with its detailed specifications.\n\n\n**Detailing Agent Attributes**\n\nI'm now detailing more agent metadata. I'm focusing on attributes like platform fit, schema, datasources, performance metrics, and system prompts. For example, the Sovereign Research Synthesizer will have its detailed specifications. I have a new agent, the Cognitive Policy Searcher, with an \"On-Premises\" platform fit and \"Factory\" GFF fit.\n\n\n**Expanding Agent Metrics**\n\nI'm now detailing more of the agents' attributes, including those of the Supply Chain Resiliency Optimizer, and I've started on system prompts and performance metrics. I'm focusing on attributes like the platform fit, schema, datasources, performance metrics, and system prompts of that agent. For example, for the Supply Chain Resiliency Optimizer I'm using \"SAP S/4HANA, Kafka Broker, Weather/Geopolitical Feeds\" as the data sources and setting the performance metric to \"94.2% Disruption Mitigation, Fully Automated.\"\n\n\n**Defining Agent Blueprints**\n\nI'm now detailing another agent: the High-Frequency Inventory Balancer, defining all attributes from use case to system prompts, with performance metrics at 35% average stockout reduction, 99.9% up-time. I'm focusing on defining the Zero-Trust Sovereign PII Guard next.\n\n\n**Defining Agent Data Structures**\n\nI'm now detailing more agent metadata, including the Zero-Trust Sovereign PII Guard. I'm focusing on defining agents, their attributes, performance metrics, and system prompts. For example, for the Zero-Trust Sovereign PII Guard, I'm defining the blueprint data, setting its use case, and defining system prompts to intercept and redact sensitive data.\n\n\n**Defining Agent Capabilities**\n\nI'm now detailing an agent: the Webhook Ingest. Its data sources are \"Workday Ledger, Internal Balance Sheets, SEC Filing Templates,\" with a performance metric of \"99.8% Audit Coverage, 12x Speed Increase,\" and a system prompt to flag discrepancies. I am also working on the Hyper-Personalized CX Broker, documenting its use case, GFF fit, and related capabilities. I'm focusing on defining agents like this to enhance their quality.\n\n\n**Defining Agent Data**\n\nI'm now detailing an agent: the B2B Service Agreement Agent. I'm focused on defining its data sources as the Contract Vault, Prometheus/Grafana Outage Log, and the CRM Store, with the performance metric of \"SLA Claim Verification Time Reduced from Days to Minutes.\" The system prompt will reconcile claim tickets with customer contracts, drafting responses based on historical uptime telemetry files. I'm also now planning for the executive agents.\n\n\n\n**Defining Agent Characteristics**\n\nI'm now detailing an agent: the Corporate Risk Agent. Its data sources are \"Snowflake Warehouse, Executive Forecast Ledger, Macro Feeds\" with the performance metric of \"99.5% Trend Projection Matching, Executive Signed Output.\" The system prompt will simulate scenarios, focusing on liquidity and cash flow with confidence bounds. I've also detailed the Venture Alignment Strategy Agent. I'm focusing on defining agents like this to enhance their quality and precision.\n\n\n**Defining Agent Properties**\n\nI'm now detailing an agent: the Investment Thesis Mapper. I'm focusing on defining agents like this to enhance their quality and precision. Its data sources are \"Pitchbook API, Internal Deal Pipeline, ESG Criteria Map\" with the performance metric \"80% Reduction in Early-Stage Sifting Duration.\" The system prompt evaluates investment opportunities against strict sovereign alignment standards.\n\n\n**Refining Attribute Definitions**\n\nI'm now detailing an agent: the On-Premises Compliance Auditor. Its data sources are \"S3 CAD/PDF Ingest, Document Vault S3, Engineering Spec Database, PLM Repository\" with a performance metric of \"97.9% Key-Value Extraction, Complex Table Parsing.\" The system prompt will extract parameters from engineering manuals, and flag exceptions. I'm focusing on defining agents like this to enhance their quality and precision. I've also defined the Sovereign Legal Contract Auditor.\n\n\n\n**Defining Agent Parameters**\n\nI'm now detailing an agent: the Automated Supplier Negotiation Agent. My focus is defining the agent's parameters to ensure precision. Its data sources are \"SAP Materials Manager, Vendor APIs, Historical Pricing Indexes\" with a performance metric of \"6.8% Average Cost Savings, 70% Quicker Procurement Cycles.\" The system prompt will handle price negotiations.\n\n\n**Defining Agent Specifications**\n\nI'm now detailing an agent: the Global Freight Audit Agent, including use case, GFF fit, related capabilities, and system prompt details. I'm focusing on defining the agent's parameters to ensure precision. Its data sources are \"Carrier Portals, TMS Database, Rate Contract Store\" with a performance metric of \"100% Rate Error Identification, Over $2M Leakage Prevented.\"\n\n\n**Expanding Agent Characteristics**\n\nI'm now detailing the \"Internal Mobility Matcher\" agent's metadata. Its data sources are \"Workday HCM, Skill Matrix DB, Learning Management System\" with the performance metric \"3.2x Internal Mobility Lift, 100% GDPR/PII Local Custody.\" The system prompt filters out sensitive information. I've also defined the \"HR Policy & Compliance Advisor,\" focusing on local rule parsing.\n\n\n\n**Validating Category Alignment**\n\nI'm now verifying the alignment of agent categories with the established list, and confirming filter requests. I'm focusing on ensuring seamless integration with the existing structure and user experience. The blueprint list looks perfect, and all categories match.\n\n\n**Designing the Marketplace Page**\n\nI'm now iterating on the design, aiming for a premium feel. The layout will include a hero section with sovereign registry node visualizations and animated dot patterns. I'm focusing on a refined color palette, high-quality typography, and clear visual cues. I am also planning CTAs for sandbox runs or agent contact, which I hope will enhance the user experience.\n\n\n\n"}}
