{"ts":"2026-06-26T22:06:51.561Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"mc967wks","input":{"summary":"Upgraded the `/build/marketplace` page into a premium, custom-designed, and highly interactive enterprise-grade Agent Blueprint Registry and Accelerator Catalog. \n\nHere is a summary of the accomplishments matching all UI Quality Constitution guidelines:\n1. Page Narrative: Designed an immersive 'Architectural Command Center' for sovereign, certified enterprise multi-agent patterns, workflows, and accelerators.\n2. Core Interactive Features:\n   - Dynamic Telemetry Banner: Real-time registry stats detailing active nodes, baseline OCI standards, production readiness, and compliance assurances.\n   - Comprehensive Filter & Search: Keyword search bar and 4 parameter selectors (Industry Scope, Operational Function, Maturity Stage, and Enclave Fit) plus 9 horizontal category tabs (All Patterns, Knowledge, Operations, Compliance, Customer Experience, Executive, Document Intelligence, Procurement, HR Agents).\n   - Side-by-Side Comparison Drawer & Matrix Modal: A glassmorphic bottom dock tracking selected patterns (up to 3 maximum) that opens a comparative matrix comparing tiering, use case, target scope, system prompts, and telemetry performance.\n   - Simulated Sandbox Terminal Modal: Sequential live boot logs simulating container enclaves, OCI isolation, eBPF safety shield activation, and custom predefined prompt queries to test the agent inside a containment shell.\n   - Simulated Talk-to-Agent Chat Console: Full chat simulation prompting systems architects with developer guidelines and technical requirements.\n   - GFF Anatomy Bento: Custom spotlight card layouts mapping context boundary spec, safety shields, and cryptographic locks.\n3. Quality & Continuity: Maintained full parity with GFF's Apple-like premium styling, with custom-colored glowing borders on hover according to GFF tiers (Garage = Teal, Foundry = Purple, Factory = Red). Full mobile responsiveness and accessibility.\n4. Validation: Ran local `npm run build` which compiled successfully with 0 TypeScript or linting errors.","verified":true}}}
